t: Blessed*p is every one that feareth the Lord;*s that walketh in his ways.
For*p thou shalt eat the labour of thine hands: happy shalt thou be, and it shall be well with thee.
Thy*p wife shall be as a fruitful vine by the sides of thine house: thy children like olive plants round about thy table.
Behold,*p that thus shall the man be blessed that feareth the Lord.*s
The*p Lord*s shall bless thee out of Zion: and thou shalt see the good of Jerusalem all the days of thy life.
Yea,*p thou shalt see thy children's children, and peace upon Israel.
